# Layout & Spacing Standards

All pages and components must follow these layout and spacing patterns for visual consistency.

## 1. Page Container Pattern

**Platform pages inherit padding from layout** - do NOT add additional containers unless needed:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Let platform layout handle padding
export default function TasksPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <PageHeader />
      <TaskList />
    </div>
  )
}

// ❌ WRONG - Don't duplicate padding
export default function TasksPage() {
  return (
    <div className="p-6">  {/* Layout already has padding! */}
      <PageHeader />
    </div>
  )
}
```

**Platform layout provides:** `p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8`

## 2. Max-Width Patterns

Use consistent max-widths based on page type:

| Page Type | Max Width | Usage |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| **List/Grid views** | No max-width | Full width for task lists, team grids, marketplace |
| **Detail pages** | `max-w-5xl mx-auto` | Individual task, objective, profile detail |
| **Forms** | `max-w-3xl mx-auto` | Onboarding, settings, create dialogs |
| **Settings** | `max-w-4xl mx-auto` | Settings pages, preferences |
| **Marketing** | `max-w-7xl mx-auto` | Landing pages, wide marketing content |

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Detail page with centered content
export default function TaskDetailPage() {
  return (
    <div className="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <TaskDetail />
    </div>
  )
}

// ✅ CORRECT - List view without max-width
export default function TasksPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <TaskGrid />  {/* Full width */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

## 3. Spacing Scale

**Use design system spacing utilities:**

```tsx
import { spacing } from '@/lib/design-system'

// Page sections
<div className={spacing.section}>     {/* space-y-8 */}
  
  // Card content groups
  <div className={spacing.card}>      {/* space-y-6 */}
    
    // Standard lists/stacks
    <div className={spacing.stack}>   {/* space-y-4 */}
      
      // Tight groupings
      <div className={spacing.stackTight}>  {/* space-y-2 */}
```

**Direct values when needed:**

| Use Case | Value | When to Use |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| **Page sections** | `space-y-8` | Between major page sections (header, content, footer) |
| **Card groups** | `space-y-6` | Between cards or content blocks |
| **List items** | `space-y-4` | Standard lists, form fields |
| **Tight content** | `space-y-2` | Label-to-input, related metadata |
| **Wide sections** | `space-y-12` | Marketing sections, hero spacing |

## 4. Grid Patterns

**Use consistent grid breakpoints and gaps:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Standard 3-column grid
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  <Card />
  <Card />
  <Card />
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Responsive 2-column to 4-column
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
  <Item />
</div>
```

**Grid gap standards:**

| Use Case | Gap Value |
|----------|-----------|
| **Default grids** | `gap-6` |
| **Dense grids** | `gap-4` |
| **Wide grids** | `gap-8` |

**Breakpoint preference:**
- Use `md:` and `lg:` for most layouts (not `sm:`)
- Use `sm:` only for small adjustments (typography, padding)
- Use `xl:` for 4+ column grids

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Don't use inconsistent gaps
<div className="grid gap-7">  {/* Use gap-6 or gap-8 */}
<div className="grid gap-5">  {/* Use gap-4 or gap-6 */}
```

## 5. Card Layout Pattern

**Use Card component consistently:**

```tsx
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from '@/components/ui/card'

// ✅ CORRECT - Standard card
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <p>Card content</p>
  </CardContent>
</Card>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't override card padding
<Card className="p-8">  {/* CardHeader/Content handle padding */}
  <h2>Title</h2>
</Card>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use custom card divs
<div className="rounded-lg border p-6">  {/* Use Card component */}
  <h2>Title</h2>
</div>
```

**Card component provides:**
- `CardHeader`: `p-4 sm:p-6` with `space-y-1.5`
- `CardContent`: `p-6 pt-2`
- `CardFooter`: `p-6 pt-2`

## 6. Page Header Pattern

**All platform pages must use the standardized header with orange accent bar:**

```tsx
import { typography } from '@/lib/design-system'

<div className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between gap-4 pb-4 border-b border-slate-100">
  <div className="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <div className={typography.pageHeader}>
      <div className={typography.pageHeaderAccent} />
      <h1 className={typography.h1}>
        Page Title
      </h1>
    </div>
    <p className={typography.pageSubtitle}>
      Subtitle or description
    </p>
  </div>
  
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
    <Button>Action</Button>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Header standards:**
- ✅ Orange accent bar on all platform pages
- ✅ Responsive flex layout (column on mobile, row on desktop)
- ✅ Border: `border-slate-100` (not blue or foundry variants)
- ✅ Bottom padding: `pb-4`
- ✅ Typography from design system

