## 9. Content Centering

When centering content, use consistent patterns:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Centered container
<div className="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
  <Content />
</div>

// ✅ CORRECT - Flex center for single item
<div className="flex items-center justify-center min-h-[200px]">
  <EmptyState />
</div>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't mix patterns
<div className="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl">  {/* Redundant */}
```

## 10. Section Dividers

Use consistent dividers between sections:

```tsx
// Border divider
<div className="border-b border-slate-100 pb-4 mb-8" />

// Spacer divider (no visual line)
<div className="h-8" />  // Use sparingly

// Separator component (for within-card dividers)
import { Separator } from '@/components/ui/separator'
<Separator className="my-4" />
```

## Quick Checklist

Before committing any layout:

- [ ] Platform pages rely on layout padding (no duplicate `p-6`)
- [ ] Max-width follows standards (detail pages: `max-w-5xl`, forms: `max-w-3xl`)
- [ ] Page sections use `space-y-8`, card content uses `space-y-6`
- [ ] Grids use standard gaps (`gap-6` default, `gap-4` dense)
- [ ] Breakpoints use `md:` and `lg:` consistently
- [ ] Cards use Card component (not custom divs)
- [ ] Page headers have orange accent bar
- [ ] Header border uses `border-slate-100`
- [ ] No custom gap values (gap-5, gap-7)
- [ ] Responsive padding follows platform standards
